title: Judge lets Facebook privacy class action proceed, calls company's views 'so wrong'
text: A federal judge on Monday ordered Facebook Inc  to face most of a nationwide lawsuit seeking damages for letting third parties such as Cambridge Analytica access users' private data, calling the social media company's views on privacy "so wrong."

title: Facebook's Zuckerberg and Sandberg very involved in content decisions, report says
text: The social network has faced criticism for what content it leaves up or pulls down.

title: State probes into Big Tech are a 'backstop' in case the feds back down, say antitrust experts
text: Nearly all the nation's state attorneys general are probing Big Tech companies, which will likely put pressure on federal investigators.

title: 5 Large-Cap Stocks Beating the Market
text: According to the GuruFocus All-in-One Screener, the following stocks have outperformed the Standard & Poor's 500 Index over the past 12 months.

title: Facebook and Amazon are among JP Morgan's top internet picks despite regulatory scrutiny
text: J.P. Morgan likes Facebook, Amazon, Twitter, Netflix and media company IAC as its top internet sector picks in the second half of 2019.

title: Facebook insiders say Zuckerberg and Sandberg are involved in content decisions ‘all the time’
text: High level executives at Facebook talk to Yahoo Finance's Editor-in-Chief Andy Serwer about how involved Sheryl Sandberg and Mark Zuckerberg are in content decisions at Facebook.

title: Should you trust Facebook with your secret crush?
text: Facebook’s FB, -0.72%   flirtation with matchmaking could serve up certain perks for singles, but users should still think twice before sharing intimate data with the scandal-scarred tech giant, privacy experts warn.

title: Florida's attorney general: There's no 'case study' for our multistate Facebook antitrust probe
text: "It's an entirely different way of dealing with a monopoly," says Florida's Ashley Moody, just days after the state revealed its participation in a multi-jurisdictional probe.

title: Florida AG Ashley Moody on probes into Google, Facebook
text: Florida Attorney General Ashley Moody joins "Squawk on the Street" to discuss the multi-state antitrust probes into Google and Facebook.

title: Facebook and Instagram downloads are declining, Bank of America analysis says
text: Mobile app downloads of Facebook are down 15% year over year so far in the third quarter of 2019, a Bank of America analysis found.

title: Mewawalla: Big Tech hasn't been taking regulation seriously
text: Cyrus Mewawalla of GlobalData discusses the impact the increased regulatory scrutiny of Google, Facebook and other big tech companies could have on their stocks, and whether authorities could seek to break up the firms.

title: Watch out for this key level in Facebook, Piper Jaffray technical analyst says
text: Facebook is under fresh scrutiny, but the increased regulatory pressure from federal and state agencies hasn't deterred this Piper Jaffray technician.
